":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow#why-this-holds-up-well-in-production","content":"The handler body stays linear. There is no framework-specific DSL to learn."},"332":{"id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow-17","page_id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow#good-variation-add-a-remote-dependency","content":"The retry policy is attached to the flaky network call, not to the whole request."},"333":{"id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow-18","page_id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow#avoid-retrying-the-whole-handler","content":"That repeats validation, routing decisions, and any side effects. Retry the noisy boundary instead."},"334":{"id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow-19","page_id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow#rules-worth-keeping","content":"Validate early and return early."},"335":{"id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow-20","page_id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow#rules-worth-keeping","content":"Retry only the noisy boundary, not the entire request."},"336":{"id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow-21","page_id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow#rules-worth-keeping","content":"Spawn sibling work only when both tasks should die together."},"337":{"id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow-22","page_id":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/resilient-service-flow#rules-worth-keeping","content":"Map domain misses to explicit HTTP errors like `NotFoundError`."},"338":{"id":"/docs/reference/all","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","type":"page","content":"yieldless/all","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Reference","Reference"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/all"},"339":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-0","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/all","content":"Tuple-aware parallel combinators that share cancellation."},"340":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-1","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/all#exports","content":"Exports"},"341":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-2","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/all#example","content":"Example"},"342":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-3","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/all#behavior-notes","content":"Behavior notes"},"343":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-4","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/all#when-to-prefer-runtaskgroup-instead","content":"When to prefer runTaskGroup() instead"},"344":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-5","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/all#good","content":"Good"},"345":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-6","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/all#avoid","content":"Avoid"},"346":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-7","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/all","content":"`yieldless/all` gives you helpers for tuple-returning parallel work: `all(tasks)` waits for every task or aborts siblings on the first error, `race(tasks)` resolves with the first settled result and aborts the rest, and `mapLimit(items, mapper, options)` processes a collection with bounded concurrency."},"347":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-8","page_id":"/docs/reference/all","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/all#exports","content":"`type SafeTask<T, E = Error> = (signal: AbortSignal) => PromiseLike<SafeResult<T, E>> | SafeResult<T, E>`"},"348":{"id":"/docs/reference/all-9","page_id":"/docs/reference/all